# UV-Vis Bandgap Analysis

This project demonstrates optical bandgap estimation from synthetic UV–Vis absorbance data using Tauc plot analysis.

## Features
- Synthetic UV–Vis dataset
- Absorbance spectrum visualization
- Photon energy conversion
- Tauc plot generation
- Optical bandgap estimation workflow

## Physics Background
Tauc analysis is commonly used in semiconductor physics and materials science to estimate the optical bandgap of thin-film materials from UV–Vis spectroscopy measurements.

## Tools Used
- Python
- NumPy
- Pandas
- Matplotlib

## Applications
- Semiconductor thin films
- Transparent conducting oxides
- Optoelectronic materials
- UV-active oxide systems

